>>>>> ## Join us as a volunteer in the South West
>>>>> From Land’s End to Lydney, Swindon to the Scilly Islands, our great team
of over 400 volunteers are vital to everything we do here at Diabetes UK.
>>>>> Every year our volunteers help hundreds of people find out their risk of
developing diabetes; they give inspirational speeches, campaign for better
services, help run local support groups, organise fun events and offer much
>>>>> They are making a real difference to people living with diabetes.To find
out more about how you can volunteer to help people with diabetes, please get
in touch with our South West volunteering team:
>>>>> Diabetes UK, Victoria House, Victoria Street, Taunton, TA1 3FA
>>>>> Above: Our Warminster Local Group volunteers help the public to find out
>>>>> To find out how to get involved, go to our Volunteering Opportunities
>>>>> #### Volunteering and Outreach Manager, Verity McLelland
>>>>> I work across the South West region supporting volunteers as they learn
new skills and grow in their roles, including running local groups and raising
awareness. We train and develop volunteers so that they have the knowledge and
confidence they need to help others and make a real difference to people
affected by diabetes. There are so many ways you can get involved with us to
really help others and become part of a fantastic team.
>>>>> Please email verity.mclelland@diabetes.org.uk to get in touch.
>>>>> I work across the South West region helping to recruit and support
volunteers as they join the team. It's always such a pleasure to meet the
incredible people who are making a difference to people living with diabetes
in their local community. We have lots of volunteering opportunities
available, so please get in touch to find out more.
>>>>> Please email gemma.jackson@diabetes.org.uk to get in touch
>>>>> Bristol, Cornwall, Devon, Dorset, Gloucestershire, Somerset, Swindon,
>>>>> Contact the South West team at south.west@diabetes.org.uk
